<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, January 20 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami has reiterated
that there is no need for Iran to resume ties with the United
States since Washington still adopts hegemonist policies.
</P>
<P>
According to the official news agency IRNA Tuesday, Khatami
made the remark Monday night while addressing a large group of
people at the mausoleum of the late spiritual leader Ayatollah
Khomeini.
</P>
<P>
"Today we do not need to have the United States at our side, we
can go ahead without the help of the United States," he said,
accusing Washington of "behaving like lords of the world and
imposing sanctions on every country."
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- The current economic crisis in Asia is expected
to take center stage at the Second Asia-Europe Meeting (ASEM) to
be held in London next April, Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah
Ahmad Badawi said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
With the introduction of the single European currency next
year, the currency depreciation and economic crisis in this region
were crucial, he told reporters after meeting an 11-member
European Union (EU) parliamentary delegation led by Gunter Rinsche
of Germany.
</P>
<P>
ASEM is a forum which groups 15 EU member countries, China,
Japan, South Korea and several ASEAN countries.
</P>
<P>
Badawi said that he took the opportunity to explain to the
visitors that ASEAN was united in tackling the economic woes and
the weakening of the region's currencies and in boosting
intra-trade among them.
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesian President Soeharto on Tuesday expressed
his readiness to run for the presidency for the 1998-2003 period.
</P>
<P>
"AL-HAJ Mohamad Soeharto is prepared to be renominated for
presidency in the upcoming general session of the People's
Consultative Assembly for the 1998-2003 term of office," General
Chairman of the ruling Functional Group (Golkar) Harmoko announced
at the Bina Graha Presidential Office here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
