<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Determined to Extend Territorial Waters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Greece today expressed its
determination to the extension of its territorial waters beyond
the current six-mile limit despite the increased pressure from
neighboring Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Greek government spokesman
Dimitris Reppas stressed that it had the "inalienable right" to
extend its territorial waters to twelve miles and would do so
whenever it saw fit.
</P>
<P>
Turkey reportedly voiced its opposition to the decision by
Athens to extend its territorial waters on Monday, saying that
such an extension would contravene international law as well as
the spirit of the agreement signed in Madrid last July between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Reppas said that it was not possible for Turkey to cite
international agreements when Turkey itself now "violates
international law both outside the country and domestically."
</P>
<P>
He added that Athens' choices were in line with with that which
was in force internationally and in this sense there was no
question of "our negotiating with anyone our right to extend our
territorial waters to twelve miles." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
