<HEADLINE> Uganda, Netherland Sign Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Uganda and Netherland signed a
development cooperation agreement today to boost their existing
relations, the Uganda News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Eriya Kategaya, the Ugandan First Deputy Prime Minister and
Foreign Minister, and Hans Van Mierlo, the Deputy Prime Minister and
Foreign Minister of Netherland, signed the agreement on behalf of
their respective governments. The Dutch foreign minister arrived
here yesterday for a three day visit to Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Before the signing ceremony, the two officials had talks on
Uganda's infrastructure development, regional integration, and
peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
Kategaya said that Uganda is keen to restore peace in the
north where Sudan-supported rebels lauched a 11-year guerrila war
against the Ugandan government.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni also Met Hans Van Mierlo
today and held talks on the cooperation between the two countries
and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch foreign minister will visit the West Nile Region
tomorrow where Netherland has major projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
