<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Germany's largest aviation group
Daimler-Benz Aerospace AG announced Tuesday that it is swinging
back to profit after expanding sales by 20 percent to a record of
15.3 billion marks (8.3 billion U.S. dollars) in 1997.
</P>
