mee012007hke -- Lebanese Pound Devaluation Predicted
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Merrill Lynch, one of the
world's leading investment banks, has turned thumbs down to a
strong Lebanese pound, the lynchpin of the Lebanese government's
economic policy, the Daily Star newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a report, the firm warned against investing in long-term
Lebanese pound instrumens, saying the Lebanese pound is facing
risks of devaluation in the future if the government does not make
policy adjustmeely in the next three months after Lebanese central bank
reserves were bolstered by a 600 million U.S. dollars capital
injection from Saudi Arabia in December.
</P>
<P>
The central bank is finalizing another 400 million U.S. dollars
deal from the Gulf, it said.
</P>
<P>
However, Antoine Papadopodo, a financial engineer at Lebanon
Invest, a leading Beirut securities firm, downplayed the
likelihood of the currency's devaluation.
</P>
<P>
He predicted the Lebanese pound would continue to appreciate,
even when most of the world's currencies are succumbing to the
dollar. 
</P>
