<HEADLINE> Iranian Human Rights Body Condemns Turkish Islamic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Islamic Human Rights
Commission (IHRC) Tuesday condemned the closure of the Turkish
pro-Islamic Welfare Party and violation of Turkey's Muslims
rights, the Iranian official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the IHRC termed the closure of Turkish Islamic
party as the most regrettable events in Turkey during the last few
months.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Constitutional Court Friday closed the Welfare
Party, Turkey's biggest party in the National Assembly led by
former Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan, on charges of violating
the secularist tenets of the Turkish Republic.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish court's rule was considered by mass media here as a
measure against Islamic movement. But the Iranian government has
so far remained silent toward the issue.
</P>
<P>
The statement expressed the hope that the rights of the Turkish
people will be fully preserved immediately.
</P>
<P>
The IHRC was founded in 1995 with the aim of defending the
Iranian government against Western accusation over human rights
issues. After Mohammad Khatami was elected Iranian President in
May 1997, the IHRC has become more active. 
</P>
</TEXT>
