<HEADLINE> Israel's Deputy PM Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Deputy Prime Minister
Zevulun Hammer died of cancer at the age of 61 Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Hammer, also the Minister of Education, Culture and Arts, is
the leader of the National Religious Party (NRP), which is part of
the current Israeli coalition government.
</P>
<P>
The NRP, with nine members in the 120-seat Knesset
(parliament), opposes any further Israeli troop redeployment in
the West Bank if the Palestinian side does not fulfill its
commitment in fighting terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, who is on a visit to the
United States, expressed his condolence from Washington to
Hammer's family, saying Hammer has contributed a great deal to
national unity.
</P>
<P>
Opposition Labor Party leader Ehud Barak also expressed his
grief over the passing-away of Hammer, adding that Hammer has
done an excellent job in promoting unity among the Jewish people.
</P>
<P>
A special memorial service for Hammer was held in the Knesset
Tuesday afternoon before the funeral, which took place at the
Mount of Olives, Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Hammer was married with four children. 
</P>
