<HEADLINE> Super EuroLeague on the Cards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 21 (Xinhua) -- An European Basketball Super
League, Europe's equivalent of the NBA tournament, will be set up
on the turn of the century to challenge its much successful
American counterpart, according to reports from the Russian-Tasse
News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The International Amateur Basketball Federation (FIBA)
announced on Wednesday that they are set to transform the current
EuroLeague into a more appealing one which could attract bigger
money and larger following crowds.
</P>
<P>
Major European basketball clubs leaders will meet at the FIBA
Headquaters in Munich, German on January 23 to discuss the
proposal and form a working pannel to handle the matter.
</P>
<P>
Under the FIBA's plans, a total of 24 clubs from 12 countries
will make up the Super EuroLeague competitors, with each country
not able to send more than two teams.
</P>
<P>
Country's records at the major European tournaments will decide
the qualifying berths while a soft policy will apply to the
underdog countries which have strong economic background such as
the Netherlands, Sweden and Norway, FIBA said.
</P>
<P>
FIBA believe those countries will pump more money into the game
when the traditional powerhouses such as Italy, Spain and Turkey
have hit their balance sheet break-even point. 
</P>
</TEXT>
