<HEADLINE> Beijing Developing High-Technology to Boost Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- While China is facing the
pressing issue of building a robust and highly efficient economic
structure at the turn of the century, its capital is focusing on
developing high-technology and related industries.
</P>
<P>
At the first session of the 11th Beijing Municipal People's
Congress which ended here today, Beijing's Mayor Jia Qinglin said
that high-technology and related industries should be given
priority for they are the key areas in economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has the intellectual and industrial potential for
developing high-tech industries, the mayor said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Beijing has nearly 100 colleges,
universities and research institutions. And about 10 percent of
its residents are scientists or technicians.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning of China's reform and opening-up, some experts
and technicians came out of their studies and built a "computer
street" at Zhongguancun in western Beijing, which was later
referred as the cradle of Beijing's high-tech industry. During the
following two decades more, more state, private and overseas
investors flocked to Beijing's new industries.
</P>
<P>
According to the Beijing Association for Science and
Technology, the number of high-technology enterprises in the city
has exceeded 6,000, with foreign enterprises reaching 1,000.
</P>
<P>
Legend Computer Group Co., based on Zhongguancun, has become
China's personal computer giant and its second largest electronic
enterprise. Stone Corp., founded in 1984, has expanded its
business from manufacturing lighting equipment to developing
computer software and trade, grossing 6.5 billion yuan (780
million U.S. dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
At present, most of the city's high-tech enterprises are in
Beijing's pilot and economy and technology development zones. The
high-technology industry development pilot zone generated 10
percent of the city's GDP last year.
</P>
<P>
Jia said that Beijing's high-tech development should be led by
the information industry and such new industries as electronics,
bioengineering, and pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
High-technology will also be applied to rejuvenating
traditional industries and improving their technological level,
the mayor said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
