<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Eight kidnap suspects were
killed Wednesday in two separate shootouts with police in Caloocan
city, Metro Manila, the Philippine National Police said.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigation suggested that those suspects belonged to
a kidnap-for-ransom syndicate operating in the capital area,
police said.
</P>
<P>
Four of the eight suspects, who were believed responsible for
an earlier kidnapping, were killed in an encounter with police
Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The other four were also killed in an alleged safehouse of the
syndicate by an anti-kidnap police force hours later.
</P>
<P>
Police said they trailed the four suspects from Quezon city,
another part of Metro Manila, where the kidnappers received
200,000 peso ransoms.
</P>
<P>
Kidnap-for-ransom syndicates have been rampant in the
Philippines in recent years. More than 200 kidnapping cases were
reported to the police in 1997.  
