<HEADLINE> Beijing-based Journalists Look Back at 1997, Ahead to 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- With a lot of big events
happening in China, 1997 was a busy yet exciting year for
journalists working in the country.
</P>
<P>
That was the feeling expressed by journalists attending a new
year's gathering held here today by the All China Journalists'
Association (ACJA).
</P>
<P>
Gilles Campion, Beijing Bureau chief of Agence France-Presse,
said the past year was the busiest since he came to China five
years ago. Campion referred to the historical events of Deng
Xiaoping's passing, Hong Kong's return to China and the
convocation of the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party
of China.
</P>
<P>
"1997 was really very important and exciting for journalists,"
Campion said.
</P>
<P>
Looking forward to 1998, the French journalist predicted the
two big issues will be the forthcoming annual meeting of China's
National People's Congress, at which China's new chief of
government will be elected, and how China reacts to the monetary
crisis now sweeping Asia.
</P>
<P>
"With China playing an increasingly important role on the world
scene, people are hungry for information about China," said
Frederic Bobin, China correspondent for the French newspaper Le
Monde.
</P>
<P>
Agreeing with his French colleague, Joseph Anil, China
correspondent for Press Trust of India, said that what journalists
are doing is closing the information gap between China and the
rest of the world by getting more information about China to the
public.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the gathering, ACJA Chairman Shao Huaze called 1997
"a most extraordinary year in the history of our Party and our
country"
</P>
<P>
Over the past year, he said, Chinese journalists made new
achievements in reporting on China's modernization drive and
increasing the understanding and friendship between Chinese and
overseas journalists.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his appreciation of overseas journalists'
efforts in presenting China's achievements to the world and
enhancing the understanding and friendship between the Chinese
people and people around the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
