<HEADLINE> Manila to Host Major ASEAN Meetings in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines will host four
major meetings of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN) from July 21 to 29, including the ASEAN Ministerial
Meeting and the ASEAN Regional Forum.
</P>
<P>
The 31st ASEAN Ministerial Meeting and the 5th ASEAN Regional
Forum will be held on July 24-25 and July 27 respectively, the
Philippine News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The other two meetings are the ASEAN Standing Committee Senior
Officials Meeting on July 21-22 and the Post Ministerial
Conference on July 28-29.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers and other senior officials of the nine ASEAN
member countries and those of their dialogue partners will
converge in Manila for these meetings.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN presently groups Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia,
Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam. The
Philippines, which currently holds the chairmanship of ASEAN, will
preside over all these meetings.
</P>
<P>
Expected to attend the Regional Forum and the Post Ministerial
Conference are high-level representatives from the 10 ASEAN
dialogue partners -- Australia, Canada, China, the European Union,
India, Japan, South Korea, New Zealand, Russia and the United
States.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from Cambodia and Papua New Guinea are also
expected to take part in the four meetings as observers.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN Regional Forum is the only existing dialogue forum in
Asia where security issues and related modes of cooperation are
discussed.
</P>
<P>
The Post Ministerial Conference, on the other hand, serves as a
plenary session among the ASEAN member countries and a venue for
bilateral and multilateral consultations with their dialogue
partners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
