<HEADLINE> Quake Victims Rebuild Homeland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHANGBEI, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Zhangjiakou City will invest
the total donation of 100 million yuan, together with World Bank's
20 million-US dollar loans, in infrastructure and economic
rehabilitation, a senior local official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The quake-hit areas should at first develop water irrigation
and conservation facilities for Zhangbei County, Cheng Weigao,
secretary of Hebei Provincial Party Committee, said after visiting
the seriously damaged county.
</P>
<P>
All the loans from the World Bank and some donations will be
used on irrigation facilities.
</P>
<P>
Hebei authorities did their best to aid the homeless people,
helping them earn an average annual income of about 1,700 yuan, or
about 200 US dollars, by the year of 2000.
</P>
<P>
The state, other provinces and businesses will help the victims
to rebuild their houses.
</P>
<P>
The city will finish the repair of schools, electric and
telecommunications facilities, said Zhang Baoyi, Zhangjiakou's
acting mayor.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake measuring 6.2 on the Richter Scale on January 10
killed dozens of farmers, damaged more than 32,800 houses, injured
10,000 people, and left more than 3,000 homeless, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Zhangbei and Shangyi counties have suffered the total loss of
about 740 million yuan, officials estimated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
