<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves 309 Million Dollars of Credit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has
approved a 309.2 million US Dollars equivalent credit to improve
roads and their management in Ethiopia, according to a news
release from the World Bank available here today.
</P>
<P>
The release said the support project is the first phase of the
International Development Association (IDA) support to the
Ethiopian government's 10-year road sector development program
which will physically restore much of Ethiopia's road network,
improve management of road agencies, and create jobs and
affordable transportation for the rural poor.
</P>
<P>
The support project's total cost of 538.1 million US Dollars,
will be financed by a 309.2 million US Dollars equivalent IDA
credit and co-financed by the Ethiopian government in the amount
of 214 million US Dollars, the balance to be made up by various
bilateral and other lenders, according to the release.
</P>
<P>
IDA is a subsidiary body of the World Bank. The IDA credit is
on standard terms of 40 years maturity, with 10 years grace
period, and 0.75 percent service charge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
