<HEADLINE> Spring Festival Travelers Pack Capital Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Peak air traffic around the
Spring Festival, the Chinese Lunar New Year and the most important
date on the Chinese calendar, has started at the Capital Airport
with a total of 420 packed flights expected to take off and land
today at China's biggest airport.
</P>
<P>
From 8-to-10 this morning, 12,000 passengers boarded planes at
Capital Airport to signal the start of the peak travel season.
</P>
<P>
According to the computer ticketing system at the airport,
bigger passenger flows are predicted on Jan. 24, 25 and 26.
</P>
<P>
Spring Festival, a time for family reunions, falls on Jan. 28
this year. Most of the passenger flow during the peak period will
be within the week before Jan. 28 and after Feb. 1, the last day
of the Spring Festival holiday.
</P>
<P>
Flight delays due to weather changes have recently been
reported in airports across China, and airport authorities here
have promised that they are prepared for all possible weather
conditions. 
</P>
