<HEADLINE> Airport Expansion Doing Well in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The Liuting Airport expansion
project is going smoothly in the port city of Qingdao in east
China's Shandong Province, a famous summer resort.
</P>
<P>
Construction on expanding the floor space of its terminal
building from 1,200 sq.m. to 3,500 sq.m. was completed Tuesday,
which cost an investment of 15 million yuan (about 1.8 million
U.S. dollars) from the city government.
</P>
<P>
Built in 1982, the Liuting Airport had a mere handling capacity
of 400,000 people annually, as against 1.77 million of real
passenger flow through the port last year, among the country's top
20.
</P>
<P>
Under the expansion project initiated last year, the airport
is projected to have an increased passenger transporting capacity
of 3.2 million and a freight handling capacity of 58,500 tons.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the length of the runway will be extended to 3,400
meters from the present 2,600 meters and a 120,000-sq.m. parking
lot built. Meanwhile, relevant airport facilities will be
upgraded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
