have recently seized a large number of counterfeit leather bags
and pirated compact discs in a string of operations against
infringement on intellectual property rights.
</P>
<P>
Calvin Leung Ho, head of the Intellectual Property
Investigation Bureau, said at a news briefing Wednesday that his
officers had smashed a distribution network of faked leather bags,
confiscating 11,000 articles.
