<HEADLINE> Sampras Eases Through into Third Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- World No.1 Pete Sampras easily
disposed of Italian David Sanguinetti in Melbourne Wednesday to
reach the third round of the Australian Open tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Sampras took just 70 minutes to beat Sanguinetti, ranked 94th
in the world, 6-2 6-1 6-2.
</P>
<P>
The world top player dominated the court and never gave his
opponent a chance to break into the match.
</P>
<P>
Sampras said after the match he felt good throughout, although
his serve had not been at its potent best in the cold, heavy
conditions.
</P>
<P>
He also admitted the surprise loss of Australian Mark
Philippoussis earlier Wednesday to Moroccan Hicham Arazi would
help him.
</P>
<P>
"You're not looking that far ahead, but he's definitely someone
who's very dangerous when he gets his game going," Sampras said of
the Australian.
</P>
<P>
Also on Wednesday, Patrick Rafter and Mark Philippoussis of
Australia were defeated by Pablo Albano of Argentina and Alex
Corretja of Spain 3-6 6-3 5-7. 
