<HEADLINE> Shanghai Insurance Business Reaps 8.759 Billion Yuan in Premiums </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's insurance business
reaped 8.759 billion yuan (1.05 billion U.S. dollars) in premiums
last year.
</P>
<P>
Chinese insurance companies got 8.159 billion yuan in premiums,
up 53.6 percent from last year, Wang Huaqing, deputy governor of
the Shanghai Branch of the People's Bank of China, here today.
</P>
<P>
Life insurance is the fastest-growing sector in the business,
said Wang, adding that companies based in Shanghai, both Chinese
and overseas, earned 5.721 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
Wang expects competition in the life insurance market to
intensify in 1998, and the participation of overseas-funded
insurance companies in the market to enhance the vitality and
competition in the market.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-five percent of overseas-funded companies that are
applying for business licenses in Shanghai are in life insurance,
and the three Sino-overseas joint insurance companies that have
been approved will go into business this year.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 14,000 certified insurance agents in
Shanghai, and two more examinations for more agents will be held
this year, Wang said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
