<HEADLINE> Philippine Ruling Party Names Vice Presidential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
announced Wednesday that Senator Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo will be
the candidate of the ruling Lakas-NUCD party for the country's
vice president in the May general elections.
</P>
<P>
Ramos made the announcement after Macapagal-Arroyo's tiny KAMPI
party formally merged with the Lakas-NUCD (National Union of
Christian Democrats) led by the president.
</P>
<P>
Macapagal-Arroyo, a proclaimed presidential aspirant and one of
the top-notchers in many opinion polls, took her oath as a member
of the Lakas before Ramos Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The Lakas-KAMPI merger, finalized after nearly one month of
negotiations, was a precondition for Macapagal-Arroyo to be the
running mate of the Lakas party's presidential candidate Jose de
Venecia, speaker of the House of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
At the merger ceremony, Macapagal-Arroyo said she made her
decision to join the ruling party after a series of consultations
with her party mates and many religious leaders.
</P>
<P>
Macapagal-Arroyo declared herself the presidential candidate of
her own party in November last year, but many had doubted she
would win the coming presidential polls because her party was too
weak.
</P>
<P>
Ramos is to proclaim the de Venecia-Macapagal-Arroyo tandem and
the ruling party's 12 senatorial lineup at the Lakas national
convention on Saturday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
