<HEADLINE> Sudan accuses US of supplying Rebels with mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, January 21 (Xinhua) -- A Sudanese security official
has accused the United States of supplying the Sudan People's
Liberation Army (SPLA), the rebel movement in southern Sudan, with
mines.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese newspaper "Akhbar El-Yom" Wednesday quoted the
official who declined to be named as saying that the supplies had
been delivered to the rebel forces through the U.N. aircraft
carrying relief supplies from Uganda to Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The official said, "The U.N. aircraft are involved in carrying
these mines from Uganda to Sudan under the guise relief supplies."
</P>
<P>
The official pointed out that these mines will be on display
within a few days after they are removed from where they are
planted.
</P>
<P>
The SPLA guerillas have been fighting with government forces in
the south of the country for more autonomy rights from the Islamic
government for the southerners who are mostly Christians. 
</P>
