<HEADLINE> Quake-Stricken Area and Social Welfare Receive Donations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Five enterprises and a charity
groups from China's interior areas, Hong Kong and Taiwan today
provided donations worth several million yuan for the
quake-stricken areas in Zhangjiakou of Hebei Province and China's
elderly's and children's welfare.
</P>
<P>
The donations were received by the China Charity Federation
(CCF), China Senior Citizens Foundation and China Children's
Foundation.
</P>
<P>
Zhangjiakou, a major city in northern Hebei, was hit by a
magnitude 6.2 tremor on January 10, which damaged over 100,000
houses and left tens of thousands of people homeless.
</P>
<P>
To assist the reconstruction in the quake-afflicted region,
Guangzhou Jockeys' Club, a charity group from south China's
Guangdong Province, donated one million yuan (about 120,000 US
dollars) to the CCF.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, two companies from Beijing and Hong Kong donated
7,600 woollen blankets and 500 cotton overcoats to the homeless
people to fight the bitter cold of north China's winter, and a
food company from Taiwan donated 1,000 boxes of instant noodles.
</P>
<P>
A CCF official said that all the donated blankets, overcoats
and food have arrived at the quake-stricken area.
</P>
<P>
Two pharmaceutical companies in Beijing and Hebei Province
today donated their own products to the senior citizens and
children's foundations.
</P>
<P>
The medicines, with a market value of 1.05 million yuan, are
said to be good for old people's health and children's growth.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wenfan, president of the China Senior Citizens
Foundation, noted that it is the traditional virtue of the Chinese
to esteem and support the elderly.
</P>
<P>
"With the backing of the whole society, we have scored
remarkable achievements in seeking benefits for the elderly people
in the past year," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that the foundation would distribute the donations it
received today to senior citizens associations in 20 provinces
across the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
