<HEADLINE> 45 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- A total of 45 rebels of
the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party have been killed in recent
military operations staged by the Turkish security forces in
southeastern Turkey, an official statement said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency of
the Regional Rule said that the government troops had clashed
with the PKK militants in the region, killing 20 in Gabar
Mountain and one in Hamamboazi area in Sirnak province and 24
in Kulp town of Diyarbakir province.
</P>
<P>
Eight soldiers of the security forces were also killed in
the armed clashes with the PKK in the Gabar Mountain, it
added.
</P>
<P>
The statement pointed out that the government troops had
captured eight PKK rebels in the provinces of Batman, Diyarbakir
and Mardin and five PKK guerrillas had surrendered to the
security forces in the provinces of Hakkari and Sirnak.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 13-year-old separatist war for
an independent state, which has claimed over 28,000 lives in
conflicts in eastern and southeastern Turkey since August 1984.
</P>
</TEXT>
