<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Green Rally" to Highlight Environment-Friendly Cars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- China will hold an
international "green rally" in July to provide auto manufacturers
an opportunity to present their environment-friendly cars and
draw closer public attention to reducing car pollution.
</P>
<P>
Contestants of the rally will start in Guangdong Province's
Zhuhai, an environmental protection model city, for Beijing on
July 1, and drive 3,200 kilometers across Guangdong, Hunan, Hubei,
Henan and Hebei provinces, and Tianjin City within two weeks.
</P>
<P>
Instead of racing cars, the rally will only involve
environment-friendly cars, which are currently in use or will be
put in use soon. Contestants will be judged by environment indexes
about their cars, tested during the race.
</P>
<P>
Advertisement of the prevention and control of car pollution
will be carried out in provinces and municipalities, which the
race will cover.
</P>
<P>
The output of China's auto industry has been increasing at an
average annual rate of 20 percent since 1991. The number of
automobiles in the country has exceeded 11 million. Experts
predicted that more and more families will buy cars in the next
five to ten years.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China has taken tough measures to check increasingly
serious car pollution. Beijing and some other big cities banned
the use of petrol with lead-content last year, and the unleaded
petrol will be in use all over the country by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The rally, the first of its kind in China, will be sponsored
jointly by the State Environment Protection Agency, and the State
Physical Culture and Sports Commission, and the State Science and
Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
Some 16 Chinese and foreign auto manufacturers, including the
German Volkswagon Co. Ltd, have already expressed their intention
of attending the contest.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
