<HEADLINE> China To Increase Financial Sector Reforms (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
by Xu Xingtang
</P>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- As a major step to reform the
country's financial system, China will gradually close the
provincial branches of the People's Bank of China(PBOC) and set up
a number of regional branches.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese authorities are determined to continue the
nationwide reforms and have a framework for financial sector
reforms.
</P>
<P>
Major moves are a reorganization of local branches of the
central bank and state-owned commercial banks and increasing
supervision of financial institutions and markets. The ultimate
goal of the new round of reforms is a modern financial system and
a sound financial order over the next three years to keep up with
socialist market economy developments.
</P>
<P>
The People's Bank of China (PBOC) will draw on international
financial management practices for administrative reforms to
increase independence, authority, and professionalism of the
central bank, and provincial PBOC branches will be gradually
closed and a number of regional branches set up.
</P>
<P>
The local branches of the state-owned commercial banks that are
not performing well will be closed or merged, and local commercial
banks will be gradually established in large and medium-sized
cities.
</P>
<P>
Capital markets with risk funds and industrial funds will be
developed so that individual capital can be directed to
enterprises with a good record and banks will raise funds
indirectly.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
