<HEADLINE> Computerized System for Logistics Exercise Put into Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The Academy of Logistics
Command of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) has put into
use a computer-aided system to simulate logistics exercises.
</P>
<P>
In a recent logistics exercise, commanders, staff officers and
students at the academy were divided into 22 teams, each of which
represented a division.
</P>
<P>
In the 22 simulated division headquarters, more than 150
computers ran fast to process varied battle information. The large
screens of six computers, which received battlefield situation
from network computers, handled military supplies in good order.
</P>
<P>
A general in charge of the exercise said that the system is an
unprecedented success in large-scale logistics exercises of the
Chinese army.
</P>
<P>
He said that if logistics supply for 22 divisions is carried
out by servicemen in an area covering tens of thousands of sq km,
it will consume large amounts of financial, material and human
resources.  
</P>
