<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cold Spell Invades Southern City of Nanning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Nanning, capital of south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, has made a swift
transition into winter with the mercury dropping more than 20
degrees Centigrade in 10 days.
</P>
<P>
The reported low Tuesday was 4.5 degrees Centigrade, according
to the local meteorological observatory, while the high on Jan. 10
was 28.9 degrees Centigrade. The city was even battered by a
thunderstorm and hail on Jan. 14.
</P>
<P>
City residents are wearing their thick overcoats and buying new
ones, as the cold spell dispersed merchants' worries of being
overstocked with leather coats because of the warm weather.
</P>
<P>
Hot pots have become a popular meal, with peddlers selling out
of hot pot dressing and food.
</P>
<P>
Heating units, from the traditional coal fire basin to a
variety of electric appliances, have helped residents fight the
cold.
</P>
<P>
Crops suffered severely from the last week's thunderstorm and
hail and the cold spell. Vegetable prices have doubled in the last
10 days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
