<DOCNO> XIE19980121.0155 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nearly Half Beijing Households Install Telephones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Nearly half of Beijing
households have installed telephones, a sample survey released
here today said.
</P>
<P>
Today's Science and Technology Daily reported that according to
a sample survey of 214 Beijing urban households made by Beijing
Shaohai Market Survey Company, 48 percent of Beijing households
have installed telephones by June, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The survey indicates that telephones have been installed in
87.6 percent of the Beijing households, 11.4 percent of which have
two while one percent of them have three phones.
</P>
<P>
The daily newspaper says the monthly telephone charges paid by
each Beijing household range from about 1.9 US dollars to about
100 dollars and the average household telephone fees are 8.8
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The survey also indicates that households with higher income
spend about 22 dollars for phone calls monthly on an average and
middle-class families spend about 8.2 dollars for the monthly
charges.
</P>
<P>
The survey also shows that Beijing people are expecting better
service and multi-functions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
