<HEADLINE> Draft Project Agreement on HK's West Rail Endorsed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Executive
Council endorsed a draft project agreement on the construction of
the Western Corridor Railway, Nicholas Ng, secretary for
transport, announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ng said the draft document sets out how the West Rail project
will be undertaken and the respective obligations of the
government and the Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation (KCRC) in
terms of the financing, design, construction and operation of West
Rail.
</P>
<P>
According to the KCRC's latest estimation, the total project
costs are 64 billion Hong Kong Dollars (8,205 million
U.S. Dollars) which includes all capital costs, land acquisition
costs and financing costs, which is expected to be financed by a
mix of government equity, commercial borrowing and KCRC's
internal sources of funds.
</P>
<P>
Ng said: "It is our intention to seek approval in February for
a commitment to inject 29 billion Hong Kong Dollars (3,718 million
U.S. Dollars) equity into KCRC".
</P>
<P>
He described the completion of the draft project agreement as a
key milestone leading to the implementation of the West Rail
project, believing that the government's equity will help ensure a
timely delivery of West Rail, targeted at December, 2003.
</P>
<P>
The draft project agreement will be executed between the
government and the KCRC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
