<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China Railway Passes Examination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 21 (Xinhua) -- A major railway on the east
part of south China's prosperous Guangdong Province passed
national examination today.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the Guangmeishan Railway, a 480-km-long
trunkline linking Guangzhou, Dongguan, Heyuan, Meizhou, Jieyang,
Chaozhou and Shantou, was started on May 31, 1991, with
tracklaying ended on July 20, 1995, ten months ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
Over the past years, more than 11 million passengers and 12.2
million tons of cargo have been carried through the railway, with
total transportation income reaching 1.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Last year transportation income from the railway soared 78
percent to 901 million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
