<HEADLINE> Tianjin Witnesses Increased Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 21 (Xinhua) -- A total of 127 foreign ventures
increased their investments in Tianjin, the largest port in north
China, during 1997.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Tianjin Municipal Commission for Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation indicate that the ventures
increased their investments by a total of 476 million U.S. dollars
during the first ten months of last year, with the figure
accounting for 11.3 percent of the municipality's total
investments used in the January-October period.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ventures also increased their investments by 2.85 billion
U.S. dollars between 1993-1996, according to the statistics.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin, one of China's first coastal cities opened to the
outside world, has engaged in painstaking efforts to improve its
investment environment over the past few years. Related efforts
have provided an ideal environment enabling foreign investors to
earn handsome returns on their investments. 
</P>
