<HEADLINE> Liaoning Accelerates Agricultural Industrialization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The government of northeast
China's Liaoning Province has unveiled a plan to introduce 10
agricultural projects to promote industrialization.
</P>
<P>
The projects, which will require total investments of 647
million yuan, are expected to yield a combined added-value of 1.87
billion yuan and profits of 190 million yuan, according to a
provincial official.
</P>
