<HEADLINE> Gas Found in Malaysia-Thailand Joint Development Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The Malaysia-Thailand
Joint Authority (MTJA) announced Wednesday that gas has been
discovered at the Muda-5 appraisal well on the Muda gas field in
their Joint Development Area (JDA).
</P>
<P>
Gas was discovered at the Muda-5 well on December 18, 1997,
which was drilled to a final depth of 2,480 meters, MTJA said in a
statement released here.
</P>
<P>
Its contractors at JDA's Block B-17 -- PTTEP International Ltd.
and Petronas Carigali (JDA) Sdn Bhd -- have successfully
completed drilling and testing at the well on the Muda gas field
where gas was first discovered by the Muda-1 well in November 1995
in Block B-17, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Muda-5 well, located about 33 kilometers north of the
Muda-1 well in Block B-17 of the JDA, is planned to firm up the
reserves in the east central block of the Muda Field for the first
phase of gas development in Block B-19, it added.
</P>
<P>
MTJA is a statutory body vested with the exclusive rights,
powers, liberties and privileges of exploring and exploiting
petroleum resources in the JDA under the Malaysia-Thailand Joint
Acts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
