<HEADLINE> Indian Official on Growth of Aviation Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 21 (Xinhua) -- A senior Indian official
Wednesday said that India has a great growth potential in the
aviation sector and there is need to go in for joint ventures,
technical tie-ups and collaborations, both within the country and
with overseas organizations.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating an international aviation seminar in Bangalore
city of southern India, Dr. C. G. Krishnadas Nair, chairman of
Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL), said that there is need to
restructure, reengineer and plan the aviation sector to meet the
challenges of moving from a protected environment to competitive
and open market.
</P>
<P>
Civil aviation in India and Asia-Pacific is growing and there
is potential for rapid growth. Any improvement in the economy
would lead to growth in civil aviation, he said.
</P>
<P>
He called for setting up new airports, upgrading the existing
ones and building international airports to meet new mounting
demands in the country.  
