<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korean Military Helicopter Crash Kills One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, January 21 (Xinhua) -- A military helicopter of South
Korea crashed into a downtown school building here Wednesday
afternoon, killing one and seriously wounding the others aboard
the chopper, the Yonhap News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The 500-MC helicopter of the South Korean Army Air Commando,
which took off in the afternoon on a training flight, crashed onto
the roof of a four-storied school building in southwestern Seoul.
</P>
<P>
No casualties were reported over some 20 students, who were
just inside the building at the time of the crash.
</P>
<P>
The chopper's tail fell off after a pigeon hit its rudder and
kept spinning in the air before crashing, a witness said.
</P>
<P>
The military is investigating what caused the crash of the
craft which was developed in the mid-1970s by the Company Hughes
of the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
