<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dinosaur Fossils Found in Southwest China's Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Some dinosaur fossils in
Gongxian County in southwest China's Sichuan Province were
recently discovered after they had been buried under ground for
about 150 million years.
</P>
<P>
Archaeologists said that the newly found dinosaur fossils date
back to the early Jurassic age, and most of them belong to
sauropoda, a group of gigantic, plant-eating, four-footed
dinosaurs with long necks and tails. Others include theropodas,
flesh-eating dinosaurs that walked mainly on the hind legs.
</P>
<P>
Last May, a geological prospecting team found the fossils in
Gongxian County in southern Sichuan, and local governments
immediately took measures to put the fossils under protection.
</P>
<P>
Liu Baojun, academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences,
said the discovery is of great significance. So far, most of the
Jurassic dinosaur fossils found in China belong to the middle or
late period of Jurassic age, and the fossils of the early Jurassic
age are very rare.
</P>
<P>
Liu noted that similar fossils have been found in India and
some other countries, but they are not as well preserved as those
found in Gongxian County. "They provided important and sufficient
evidences for the research of the origin and evolution of
sauropoda," said Liu.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
