<HEADLINE> IWA Calls on US Congress to Back off on Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The Islamic World
Association (IWA) has called on the U.S. Congress to back off an
earlier resolution that considers Jerusalem the capital of Israel,
reports from Mecca, Saudi Arabia, said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This came in a long message sent by IWA Secretary General
Abdullah Al-Obeid to the U.S. Congress last Sunday and released
Wednesday, Kuwait News Agency reports said.
</P>
<P>
The message called on the U.S. to stop dealing with Israel in a
manner that hints the acceptance of the fait accompli imposed by
Israel in the holy city.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the U.S. Congress adopted a resolution, recognizing
Jerusalem as the undivided capital of Israel and calling for
moving the U.S. embassy from Tel Aviv to the holy city.
</P>
<P>
The IWA, which said it represents 1.25 billion Muslims in the
world, said this stance undermines the credibility of the
U.S. and involves it in international law complications.
</P>
<P>
Jerusalem is currently divided into two parts and the
Palestinians want the Arab east Jerusalem as the capital of their
future state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
