<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Better Industrial Sales Last Year for Eastern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The city of Qingdao, an old
industrial center in China's Shandong province, had industrial
sales of 83.66 billion yuan last year, up 26.3 percent from the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
The increase rate outstripped that of the total industrial
output by 0.8 percentage points, and 97.5 percent of products were
sold during the year, up 0.6 percentage points from the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
The city used to emphasize increasing output and suffered from
stockpiling of goods. But since 1996, the city has developed ways
of stopping the production of five-billion-yuan-worth of
slow-selling goods. It also supported production of 19 items with
market potential like beer, color TV sets, and air conditioners.
</P>
<P>
The city also developed new products, spending four billion
yuan in 11 technical improvement projects.
</P>
<P>
The idea of marketing is now popular in the city. The Haier
Co., a home appliances manufacturer, for example, has more than
6,000 outlets world-wide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
