senior dealer Stavros Nitis said it was the third consecutive day
the local currency had begun near that level, but proved unable to
sustain any further strength.
</P>
<P>
Nitis said the Australian dollar continued to track the
fortunes of the Japanese yen against the US dollar.
</P>
<P>
He said for the Australian dollar to reach 67 US cents, the US
dollar/yen would need to break through the 127.00 level, which he
said appeared unlikely at this stage.
</P>
<P>
At the close Wednesday, the Australian dollar was at 85.10 yen
from 85.61 in Sydney Tuesday and at 1.2144 marks, from 1.2188.
