<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Residents Taking Part In Quake Relief Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The city government of
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province, sponsored
a press conference recently, calling on its residents to
participate in the relief efforts for the quake-affected areas of
Zhangbei and Shangyi counties in north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The calling received a warm response from local people, who
donated 3,000 new cotton-padded quilts and 1,000 new cotton-padded
clothes for the quake victims.
</P>
<P>
The donated items have been transported to the quake-affected
areas.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake measuring 6.2 on the Richter Scale hit
Zhangbei-Shangyi on January 10, killing 50 people and making
hundreds of thousands of people homeless.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou citizens raised more than five million yuan (about
620,000 US dollars) for victims of the quake victims in Lijiang,
Yunnan Province, in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
