<DOCNO> XIE19980121.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anhui Accelerates Legislative Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 21 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
accelerated legislative activities in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Statistics for the past three years show that the Provincial
People's Congress has formulated, approved or amended 140
regulations, a record for the province's legislative history.
</P>
<P>
An official with the provincial people's congress noted that
priority has been placed on introducing economic laws and
regulations in order to ensure a good legal environment for local
economic construction.
</P>
<P>
The official pointed out that the number of economic
regulations submitted to the provincial People's Congress for
examination over the past five years accounted for 52 percent of
the total number of draft regulations tabled.
</P>
<P>
Over 60 percent of the laws, regulations and circulars approved
by the congress focused on safeguarding local economic development.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that the province also has enlarged its
legislative body which currently has some 1,000 staffers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
