<HEADLINE> Time Warner Chairman Winds Up China Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Gerald M. Levin, chairman of
US media giant Time Warner Inc., put an end to his China trip
today after visiting the country's biggest metropolis of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai mayor Xu Kuangdi met with Levin during his stay, and
briefed him about Shanghai's development in the field of
publishing, radio and television along with its economic growth.
</P>
<P>
According to Xu, Shanghai now boasts the world's biggest cable
television network. The mayor expressed the hope that the US media
would introduce more Shanghai programs to the US so as to let the
US people better understand about the metropolis.
</P>
<P>
Levin described Shanghai as a city full of vigor. He disclosed
that Time Warner is going to present a special program about
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Levin also held talks with celebrities of the
city's media circle and delivered a speech on the role of the US
media in Fudan University.
</P>
<P>
Levin was invited by the Chinese People's Association for
Friendship with Foreign Countries and president Jiang Zemin met
with him on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
