<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Laid-Offs Become Top Concern of Chinese Citizens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Laid-off workers and corruption
have ranked first and second among a list of problems Chinese
citizens are most concerned about, according to a survey of 5,000
residents in 10 major Chinese citizens.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted by Beijing-based Horizon Market Survey
and Analysis Corporation, said that 92.7 percent of citizens
believed that the unemployment problem is quite serious in China.
</P>
<P>
The survey also found that "environmental pollution," "crime"
and "inadequate social insurance" were among the top concerns.
</P>
<P>
It said only 34.8 percent and 22.7 percent of citizens believed
that "inflation" is serious.
</P>
<P>
Experts here attributed the citizens' concern over unemployment
to its impact on many people's daily lives.
</P>
<P>
They said the crime problem ranked fifth on citizens' list of
concerns, indicating that social security has been improved in the
country while the problem had been ranking at the top of lists in
the past few years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
