<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arbitration Services in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Municipal Arbitration
Committee has concluded over 150 cases, with the total bidding
standing at nearly 400 million yuan, since it went into operation
in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The committee, the first of its kind in the country, now has
over 230 arbitrators, including lawyers, scholars, professors and
entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
Secretary of the committee Chen Zhichun said that in handling
related cases, his committee abides by principles of respecting
the opinions of the clients, and settling disputes in accordance
with facts and related law, based on equal footing.
</P>
<P>
Chen said, some 60 percent of the cases concluded by the
committee were through mediation. Except economic disputes, cases
involving real estate, projects and finance have accounted for 70
percent.
</P>
<P>
China has established over 120 arbitration organizations since
the Arbitration Law became effective two years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
