<DOCNO> XIE19980121.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lanzhou to Attract Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Lanzhou, capital of northwest
China's Gansu province, has become increasingly popular for
overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Local statistics show that Lanzhou, once a major city along
the "silk road" in history, had established 1,137 overseas-funded
enterprises by the end of 1997. They have brought in 1.51 billion
U.S. dollars of contractual investment from 34 countries and
regions, including the United States, Japan and Thailand, as well
as Hong Kong and Taiwan. And 715 million U.S. dollars has been
utilized.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the city introduced more than 81.8 million
U.S. dollars, 55.1 million U.S. dollars of which was actually
used, according to the statistics.
</P>
<P>
The joint ventures, co-operative enterprises and wholely
overseas-funded companies operate in 28 fields, covering
petrochemical, pharmaceutical and real estate sectors. More than
61 percent are involved in production.
</P>
<P>
In order to improve the local investment environment and
attract more overseas funds, the city, which ever played an
important role in the economic and cultural interchange during the
Western Han (206B.C.- 24A.D.), has paid close attention to the
construction of infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The overseas-funded enterprises have contributed greatly to the
city's economic growth, and the city would provide more favourable
terms for overseas investors, said Vice-Mayor Yang Yongzhong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980121.0234 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anhui Province Opens Wider to Outside World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Opening wider to the outside
world has enabled east China's Anhui Province to witness
substantial growth in foreign trade and the introduction of
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The province's foreign trade volume for 1997 hit three billion
US dollars, up nine percent from 1996, with exports jumping 14
percent to 1.9 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Anhui has optimized its export mix and has in turn recorded a
dramatic rise in the export volume for industrial products.
</P>
<P>
The province attracted foreign investments totalling 771
million US dollars in 1997, up 16 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The number of overseas-funded businesses has increased
dramatically. A substantial portion of foreign investments has
gone for infrastructure construction and manufacturing projects.
</P>
<P>
The province was home to more than 3,700 overseas-funded
enterprises by the end of 1997, many of which were located in two
state-level and 19 provincial-level development zones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
