<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Mayor Says He Will Make Government More Efficient </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Mayor Jia Qinglin has
said that making a cleaner and more efficient government is an
urgent matter.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks while giving a report at the first session
of the 11th Beijing Municipal People's Congress, which is being
held here.
</P>
<P>
In his report, Jia pointed out that bureaucratism and formalism
prevent the government work from being perfect, so the municipal
govewrnment in the next five years will work to improve efficiency
and develop a more democratic and scientific approach to decision
making.
</P>
<P>
To do this, Jia said, officials will need a better
understanding of economics, finance and some other subjects. But,
most importantly, officials must serve the people whole heartedly
and do their utmost as public servants.
</P>
<P>
As the reforms continue, government departments are expected to
streamline themselves, unqualified officials will be dismissed,
and more competent people will be selected through examinations.
</P>
<P>
Jia said that the anti-corruption efforts will continue to
work for cleaner government and economic development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
