<HEADLINE> 4,000-Year Old Residence Similar to Modern Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archeologists have
discovered the ruins of 4,000-year old buildings in east China's
Jiangsu Province which are similar to modern construction.
</P>
<P>
The 100,000-square-meter ruins was found in Yunzhong, a town
near Lianyungang, a city in the northeastern part of Jiangsu. The
structure belonged to the Longshan Culture, a late Neolithic
civilization 4,000 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Archeologists have discovered remnants of four ancient
residential houses at the site. The architecture
design and building structure of the houses are similar to
farmers' houses in the province, according to the experts.
</P>
<P>
The ruins of one two-room house looks just like a popular rural
residence in the area. The house is 23 square meters with its door
facing the southwest for more sunshine in winter.
</P>
<P>
The building remnants proved that the residential design has
been followed from generation to generation, and is still in use
now.  
</P>
</TEXT>
