<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba to Increase Oil Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- In 1998, Cuba will exert more
efforts in exploring domestic oil resources in a bid to increase
production, Cuban oil department reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report said in 1998, Cuba plans to drill 17 new oil wells
compared with four wells in 1997. At present, Cuba produces 29,600
barrels of crude oil everyday.
</P>
<P>
To explore its oil resources, Cuba began to introduce foreign
investment in recent years. So far the Cuban national oil company has
reached 40 agreements on its oil exploration with foreign companies
with a total foreign investment of 250
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Cuba mainly produces diesel oil and heavy oil which can be used
in sugar, power and mining industries. And most wells also produce
natural gas that is estimated by the oil department to reach 200
million cubic meters in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Cuba used to rely on the former Soviet Union for oil supply and
now has to buy from the expensive international market, creating
somewhat economic crisis for herself.
</P>
<P>
Last year Cuba adopted the policy of self-reliance and began
to explore domestic oil wealth to reduce imports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
