<HEADLINE> Cuba's Fish Export to Double in 10 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Cuba plans to double its income
from fish export within 10 years, the Cuban Fishing Industry
Ministry said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The total fish production amounted to 136,500 tons in Cuba in
1997, 16,000 tons more than that in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The fishery sector earned 138 million U.S. dollars for the
country last year and the ministry planned to increase the output
of freshwater fish to 70,000 tons and earn 170 million dollars
this year. 
</P>
