<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wellington, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
closed slightly lower after a positive start Wednesday. But market
analysts said the market was consolidating its recent gains.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 3 points lower at 2254 with a turnover
of over 60 million dollars (35 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The index was dragged down mainly by Telecom shares, which
dropped 10 cents to 782 cents. Also weaker were Air New Zealand,
losing 3 cents to 216 cents, and Lion Nathan, falling 6 cents to
420 cents. But Fletcher Energy stayed unchanged at 625 cents.
</P>
<P>
The higher leaders included Brierley Investment, gaining 2
cents to 118 cents, and Carter Holt Harvey, climbing 3 cents to
278 cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 40 rises and 36 falls.  
</P>
