<HEADLINE> China Welcomes Foreign Investment in High-tech Sectors: Rong Yiren </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Rong
Yiren said in a meeting with a Japanese trade delegation here
today that China welcomes Japanese and all foreign companies to
invest more in China, particularly in the high-tech sectors.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with the 26th delegation of the Japan
Association for the Promotion of International Trade, led by its
chairman Yoshio Sakurauchi, he said the annual China trips by the
Japanese association have contributed to the increased mutual
understanding of the people of the two countries and to the
development of bilateral economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Rong praised Sakurauchi for the great efforts he had made over
years in promoting the economic and trade ties between China and
Japan.
</P>
<P>
Rong briefed the visitors on China's efforts to gradually
promote the reforms of the state-owned enterprises, improve the
social insurance system and to deepen the reform of the financial
system.
</P>
<P>
Sakurauchi said he was happy to visit China on the eve of
China's traditional Spring Festival and in the year which marks
the 20th anniversary of the signing of Japan-China Treaty of Peace
and Friendship.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he congratulated China for having maintained sound
economic growth and expressed the hope that continued progress
would be scored in the bilateral economic cooperation in the years
ahead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
