<HEADLINE> ADB to Hold Consultative Meetings in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
will hold consultative group meetings for the Federated States of
Micronesia, Kiribati and Marshall Islands in Tokyo, Japan on
January 26, 28 and 30, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Manila-based bank said Wednesday in a statement that these
meetings would enable the international donor community to
coordinate assistance to the developing countries of the Pacific
in promoting economic and public sector reform.
</P>
<P>
The main purpose of the meetings for Micronesia and Marshall
Islands is to review the overall progress, impact and future
directions on ongoing economic and public sector reforms.
</P>
<P>
Participants will include Australia, China, Japan, New Zealand,
the United States, the International Monetary Fund, the United
Nations Development Program, the World Bank and others. 
</P>
