<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Appoints New Air Force Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 21 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
signed a decree Tuesday, appointing General Anatoly Kornukov,
former head of the Moscow Military District air defense troops as
Russia's new air force commander-in-chief.
</P>
<P>
Kornukov will replace his predecessor General Piotr Deinikin.
</P>
<P>
Deinikin's dismissal was also announced in the presidential
decree, but the Kremlin refused to comment on his departure.
Analysts said Deinikin, 60, was dismissed because he has exceeded
his retirement age.
</P>
<P>
Kornukov, 55, has served in both the air defense forces and the
air force for a long time.
</P>
<P>
He graduated from the Chernigov Higher Military Air Force
College in 1964 and from the Air Defense Forces Academy in 1980.
</P>
