Monday for a 24-hour mission to Algeria to discuss ways to end a
wave of brutal killings in the oil-rich North African state.
</P>
<P>
Led by Britain's Junior Foreign Minister Derek Fatchett, the
mission was sent after nearly 1,100 civilian villagers were
slaughtered in Algeria in three weeks. 
