China's bid for re-entry into the World Trade Organization (WTO),
and its opposition to raising the so-called China's human rights
issue at the United Nations human rights commission.
</P>
<P>
Chen Junsheng said his visit was aimed to explore, by touring
Brazil's agricultural cooperatives, the possibilities for the two
counties to work together in tapping agricultural resources.
</P>
<P>
In his talks with Brazilian officials, the two sides agreed to
send teams of experts to each other's farm technologies, so as to
forge stronger agricultural cooperation in the future, he said.
</P>
<P>
The senior Chinese official arrived in Brazil on Sunday,
following a tour of Canada. 
