<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 21 (Xinhua) -- At least 88 people died of
diarrhea outbreak in Merauke district of Indonesia's Irian Jaya
province, and 902 others were hospitalized, local press Wednesday
quoted official sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The diarrhea outbreak was caused by severe and prolonged
drought last year, Chief of Merauke district R. Soekardjo said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
water wells and swamps that provide people with water were
subsided, the district chief said.
</P>
<P>
He said that local authority has filtered fresh water from
rivers and distributed the filtered water to residents by water
tank trucks.  
