<HEADLINE> China to Produce Self-Developed ATM-Aased Switches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 21 (Xinhua) -- A large Sino-foreign
switchboard producer recently sighed an agreement with a local
institution of higher learning on the production of a
new-generation switchboard with high data transmission speed.
</P>
<P>
The ATM-based (asynchronous transmission mode) switchboards, a
key to the construction of the future information super-highway
demanding gigantic data transmission, have become the hot research
and development project among all telecommunications powers.
</P>
<P>
With years of efforts, Beijing University of Post and
Telecommunications introduced China's first self-developed ATM
switches, codenamed BTC-9500, and put the product in trial
networking operation for two years.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Bell Corporation, one of the major switchboard joint
venture in China, plans to put the product in batch production
in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Telecom authorities expected the new cooperation between a
producer and a researcher could form new alliance so as to foster a
new production base in the high-tech area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
