<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Havel Re-elected Czech President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Havel, a 61-year-old former dissident playwright, won 99 lower
house votes from the 197 deputies present, and 47 in the 81-member
upper house as the only candidate in a second round.
</P>
<P>
His two challengers, Stanislav Fischer of the Communist Party
and Republican Party leader Miroslav Sladek failed to gain
sufficient votes to proceed to a second round.
</P>
<P>
The vote, by secret ballot, was preceded by a debate in the
ornate Spanish Hall of Prague Castle.
</P>
<P>
Havel was born the son of a wealthy building contractor on
October 5, 1936. As a dissident playwright, his plays were banned
for 20 years. He also spent some time in prison for playing a
leading role in the Charter 77 movement in 1968.
</P>
<P>
Havel, the former president of Czechoslovakia, was re-elected
first president of the Czech Republic in 1993.  
</P>
</TEXT>
