<HEADLINE> Chile Not to Give up Asian Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Chile will not give up the
Asian markets, though the financial crisis has prevailed in
Southeast Asia since last July, Chilean Foreign Minister Jose
Miguel Insulza said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting to discuss the crisis impact on Chile's economy,
Insulza said his country should strengthen its economic status in
the Asian market with a more flexible policy, because its products
have an important market in the region. He said the crisis would
be over soon.
</P>
<P>
Although the crisis has some negative impact on Chile, the
minister said that Chile's exports to Asia will not be reduced
sharply and its products will be exported to other Asian countries
and regions through Singapore and Hong Kong as secondary
markets. 
</P>
