<HEADLINE> OPEC To Discuss Countermeasures Against Sliding Oil Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The market monitoring committee
of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) will
convene a meeting in Vienna to discuss measures to prevent the
drop in oil prices, Farouk Muhammed, the spokesman for OPEC
confirmed Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The committee, composed of oil ministers from Nigeria, Kuwait
and Iran, is responsible for insuring that OPEC members comply
with quotas.
</P>
<P>
According to Muhammed, the market monitoring committee meeting
scheduled for January 26 could become a special ministerial
meeting if opec ministers from countries other than the three
mentioned attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
On January 19, the average price of OPEC seven crude oils
dropped to 14.59 U.S. dollars per barrel. The sliding oil prices
have caused concerns in OPEC member countries. 
</P>
