<HEADLINE> WHO Executive Board Chooses Five Candidates for New </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Board of the World
Health Organization (WHO) Tuesday chose five candidates for the
post of the organization's new director-general, said a WHO press
release.
</P>
<P>
The candidates, agreed in a private session of the executive
board here, are Sir George A. O. Alleyne, Gro Harlem Brundtland,
Nafis Sadik, Ebrahim Malick Samba and Uton M. Rafei.
</P>
<P>
The executive board will next meet, also in private session, to
consider the election of the new WHO head on January 26 when each
candidate will be interviewed. The executive board will vote to
select a nominee for the post on January 27.
</P>
<P>
Once the election process has been completed, the name of the
successful candidate will be announced in plenary. In May, at the
World Health Assembly, member states will be asked to confirm the
selection of the executive board. 
</P>
