<P>
ROME, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Bologna coach Renzo Ulivieri, who
had a row with former World Cup star Roberto Baggio over the
weekend, Tuesday announced in Bologna that he was quitting.
</P>
<P>
Ulivieri, who faced public flak for dropping Baggio for
Sunday's game against Juventus, said he had tendered his
resignation to club president Giuseppe Gazzoni Frascara.
</P>
<P>
The controversy between Baggio and Ulivieri exploded on
Saturday night, when the coach told Baggio he would be on the
substitutes' bench for the match against his old club.
</P>
<P>
Baggio refused and walked out, with his team going on to lose
3-1 the following day. He appeared for training on Tuesday,
regretting his actions.
</P>
<P>
Police were called to keep the situation calm after a group of
50 fans shouted insults at the coach, who did not take part in
Tuesday's training session.
</P>
<P>
Bologna chief Gazzoni Frascara was expected to clarify the
situation at the Serie A club later in the day. 
