<HEADLINE> Europe Backs U.S. Effort on Mideast Peace: Chirac </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 20 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
said Tuesday that Europe backs the effort being made by the United
States President Bill Clinton in seeking a revival of the Middle
East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Following his meeting with Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat at
the Elysee presidential palace, Chirac said the mediation being
offered by Clinton is "extremely important."
</P>
<P>
"The present situation is a sort of challenge to the human
right to live in peace. It is very dangerous for Israel, for
Palestinians, for the whole region," said Chirac.
</P>
<P>
He also said that "an immense majority of Israeli people want
peace."
</P>
<P>
"Each should make necessary efforts, but each should know that
there can be no security without peace," said Chirac in reference
to Israeli government's insistence on placing security before
peace.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, who will meet with Clinton on Thursday in Washington,
said that he had "great confidence" in the U.S. president, and
hoped that the United States can "put the peace process on track
again."
</P>
<P>
He also praised France for its support to the peace process and
said that the Palestinian authority wishes to protect the peace
process from "all joltings here and there." 
</P>
</TEXT>
