<HEADLINE> Conference on Disarmament Adopts Agenda for 1998 Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The Conference on Disarmament
adopted the draft agenda for its 1998 session here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the items to be discussed in the session are cessation of
the nuclear arms race and nuclear disarmament, prevention of
nuclear war, including all related matters, and prevention of an
arms race in outer space.
</P>
<P>
The conference will also make effective international
arrangements to assure non-nuclear-weapon states against the use
of threat of use of nuclear weapons, new types of weapons of mass
destruction and new systems of such weapon; radiological weapons.
</P>
<P>
The participants of some 60 member states will discuss the
comprehensive program of disarmament, transparency in armaments,
consideration and adoption of the annual report and any other
report, as appropriate, to the General Assembly of the United
Nations.
</P>
<P>
China's new ambassador for disarmament Li Changhe was present
at Tuesday's meeting.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 session is to take place in three parts with the first
part from January 20 to March 27, the second from May 11 to June
26 and the third from July 27 to September 9. 
</P>
</TEXT>
