<HEADLINE> Austria Nominate 106 Athletes for Nagano Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The Austrian Olympic committee
provisionally named 106 athletes on Tuesday for next month's
Nagano Olympics, including Alpine skiing's World Cup sensation
Hermann Maier.
</P>
<P>
The number of Austrian Alpine skiers travelling to Japan will
be trimmed down from 33 to 22 after the national ski federation
completes its qualifying procedures.
</P>
<P>
Controversial ski jumper Andreas Goldberger was also nominated
although he could be denied entry into Japan because he has
admitted to having tried cocaine once.
</P>
<P>
Also doubtful are Russian-born figure skater Julia Lautova and
cross country skier Mikhail Botvinov, who both obtained Austrian
nationality but have not yet been released by their former
federation.
</P>
<P>
Dutch-born speed skater Marnix ten Kortenaar, who became an
Austrian citizen on Tuesday, has a similar problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
