<HEADLINE> IFC Joins Peace Technology Fund for West Bank, Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today announced that it will join hands with
some other institutions in setting up a first-of-kind Peace
Technology Fund (PTF) to boost private sector activity in the West
Bank and Gaza.
</P>
<P>
Also participated by the Peres Center for Peace, Capital
Investment Management Corporation and Evergreen Canada Israel
Investment Ltd, the Fund's purpose is to form partnerships between
Palestinian and Israeli investors and also bring in the
international community to invest in a broad range of sectors.
</P>
<P>
A Memorandum of Understanding to this effect was signed in
Paris today by all parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
The PTF is structured on a representational basis, bringing
together international Palestinian and Israeli private sector
investors and managers. The committed capital from the private
sector will be 100 million dollars, with 30 percent from
Palestinian/Arab investors, 30 percent from Israeli investors, 30
percent from international investors, and a minimum 10 percent
commitment from IFC.
</P>
<P>
The PTF will invest primarily in small and medium-sized
companies across a broad range of high tech and high value-added
industrial sectors in the West Bank and Gaza, including companies
located at the Gaza Industrial estate.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and also the largest
multilateral source of equity and loan financing for private
sector projects in developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
