<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Emergency Flood Project for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a 42 million U.S. dollar loan for Argentina's emergency
flood project.
</P>
<P>
The loan is provided to help Argentina with emergency response
to El Nino in the provinces bordering the Uruguay and Parana
rivers and in the provinces of the northwestern Andean region of
the country.
</P>
<P>
The loan is part of a 60 million dollar project, which is also
financed with 18 million dollars from 12 participating Argentine
provinces.
</P>
<P>
El Nino has been felt in Argentina for several months producing
flooding that has displaced thousands of people from their homes
in the large Parana River Basin in Argentina, especially along the
high-banked Uruguay River, which rarely floods. The country is now
bracing for the effects of El Nino which is expected to produce
torrential rain and mud-slides in the Andean provinces of
Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The project is the third El Nino related project that the World
Bank has financed in Latin America and the Caribbean. Projects
have also been approved for Ecuador and Peru. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
